//Running a file

node <FileName>
//Reading a file
fs.readFile()
//Writing a file can also be used to update everything in a file. Non-blocking
fs.writeFile()
//Blocking
fs.readFileSync()
//Updating file without deleting anything
fs.appendFile()

fs.rename('old file name', 'new file name')
//Delete file
fs.unlink('file name')


//Extra
In Node Application, any async function accepts a callback as the last parameter and a callback function accepts an error as the first parameter. Let's revisit the previous example again. Create a text file named input.txt with the following content.

fs.readFile('input.txt', function(err,data){});





npm init to start a node project

to set some valu npm config set init.author.name "NAME"

npm init -y // To set the fields

npm outdated // used to check outdated packages in npm

npm outdated -depth=1 // Goes inside and checks 

npx // mocks

node --prof index // to generate logs
node --prof <file name genrated > > analyses.log

